DISTRIBUTION. — The Red Sea and the Indian Ocean, from East Africa to Indonesia , including eastern Arabia “in corals” (
Bosch et al . 1995
). Throughout the tropical Pacific Ocean ( Cernohorsky 1972 ), including Hawaii ( Kay 1979 ) and Easter Island (Rehder 1980), extending in the eastern Pacific to the Galapagos Islands (Finet 1994) and the American west coast (Keen 1971). New Caledonia , Loyalty Islands and Loyalty Ridge, live in 4-40 m , empty shells intertidal to 62 m ; Futuna Island , an empty shell in 100-110 m , probably drifted from shallower habitat.
